VIte is a modern way of developing react applications ,, its faster and developer freindly

Steps
1. Initialize a project
npm create vite@latest my-app -- --template react
npm install
npm run dev

my-app/
├── public/
│   └── vite.svg            ← Static assets
├── src/
│   ├── App.jsx             ← Main component
│   ├── main.jsx            ← Entry point, renders App -- uses ReactDOM.createRoot()
│   └── components/         ← (Your future components)
├── index.html              ← App root div
├── vite.config.js          ← Vite config
├── package.json

Importat Vote concepts
Vite uses ES modules, so all imports use relative paths or aliases (@/).
For environment variables, use .env and prefix with VITE_, e.g., VITE_API_URL.
CSS modules, TypeScript, and JSX all work out of the box.